# The `break` Keyword

Sometimes, you find what you're looking for inside a loop, and you don't need the loop to keep running.

The `break` keyword INSTANTLY stops and destroys the loop!

```dart
for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
  if (i == 5) {
    break; // Loop stops COMPLETELY at 5!
  }
}
```

## The `continue` Keyword

What if you just want to skip ONE specific round of the loop, but keep going with the next ones?

Use `continue`! It acts like a "Skip Turn" card in Uno.

```dart
for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
  if (i == 3) {
    continue; // Skips printing 3!
  }
  print(i);
}
```

slides.codeSnippet:
void main() {
  for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
    if (i == 3) continue; // Skip 3
    if (i == 5) break;    // Stop at 5

    print(i);
  }
}
